Quote:  Cheaper projects such as the new Tranz-Alpine Express - Christchurch to Greymouth and back, daily - courageously ignore the fact that New Zealand has the population of one medium-sized city spread over a landscape larger than Great Britain... From Springfield the Tranz-Alpine Express jistifies its name, all but hovering over the upper Waimakariri River as it climbs into a magical world of high mountains spectacularly snow-clad in winter, spectacularly barren in summer.
